        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "This purpose statement overstates the branch model: the repo also supports `plan/<id>` branches for planning-only flows, and those branches are still first-class in the workflow (`.claude/commands/track/pr.md:4-17`, `.claude/commands/track/plan.md:228`). As written, the convention reads as if every track must work on `track/<track-id>` only, which is not true for the planning branch path.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "knowledge/conventions/branch-strategy.md",
              "line": 5,
              "category": "correctness"
            },
            {
              "message": "This states that `metadata.json` is the SSoT for progress, but the current implementation keeps task state in `impl-plan.json` and derives status from that file: `TransitionTaskUseCase` writes only `impl-plan.json` and leaves `metadata.json` untouched (`libs/usecase/src/lib.rs:90-99`), and `ImplPlanDocument` is explicitly the Phase 3 SSoT (`libs/domain/src/impl_plan.rs:1-5`). The lifecycle convention should name `impl-plan.json` as part of the source of truth, otherwise it points editors at the wrong file.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "knowledge/conventions/track-lifecycle.md",
              "line": 5,
              "category": "correctness"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:94cdaafc0b9e126148fb1273222b14e3d457a73f93d60e69fd85cef007982d9a",
          "at": "2026-06-17T02:43:09Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`branch-strategy.md` still treats `plan/<id>` as a live branch class (`Purpose`, `Scope`, and `現在のトラック解決`), but the current resolver only accepts `track/<id>` and explicitly rejects `plan/*`, and the active-track ADR says the plan-only lane was removed. This makes the new convention internally inconsistent with the repo’s actual branch model and will mislead workflow decisions. Remove `plan/<id>` from this convention or mark it as historical only.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "knowledge/conventions/branch-strategy.md",
              "line": 5,
              "category": "correctness"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:3906fe53d9ba9f9400d32244e2d6deb73a3b347ca233a16cd14baa388238f000",
