            {
              "message": "This convention says `main` resolves the latest track via the `updated_at` legacy fallback, but the current resolver it points readers to accepts only `track/<id>` branches and returns `NotTrackBranch` for `main`. Keeping this stale rule will send users and automation down a non-existent path for current-track resolution on `main`; update the convention to match the strict resolver or point to the actual fallback path if one still exists elsewhere.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "knowledge/conventions/branch-strategy.md",
              "line": 18,
