              "message": "The migrated typestate guidance now says any state transition should prefer typestate, but the surviving Decision Flow above still tells readers to use an enum to limit state transitions. That leaves two conflicting rules in the same convention and can steer later type-design work toward the wrong abstraction. Update the Decision Flow to distinguish finite state/data variants from transition modeling, or point it at the typestate section.",
