              "message": "Deleting this rule leaves live harness-policy references pointing at a file that no longer exists. The accepted deviations only cover historical track/spec records and follow-up-deleted docs, but current operational docs still cite `.claude/rules/04-coding-principles.md`, including `.harness/capabilities/type-designer.md:84`, `.harness/capabilities/spec-designer.md:78`, `.harness/capabilities/impl-planner.md:73`, `.claude/commands/track/plan.md:260`, `knowledge/conventions/type-designer-kind-selection.md:233`/`:320`, and `knowledge/conventions/impl-delegation-arch-guard.md:116`. Agents following those instructions will chase a deleted source instead of the new `knowledge/conventions/*` documents.",
