              "message": "README now instructs first-time users to run `/track:adr2pr <feature>`, but the actual `.claude/commands/track/adr2pr.md` command does not declare or consume an argument and describes a prepared-ADR flow that auto-decides the track slug. Since README is becoming the sole human-facing entry point, this non-canonical command shape can mislead users into passing a feature argument that is ignored. Drop `<feature>` here or update the command definition to explicitly accept and use it.",
